"Hello" is a common English greeting or salutation first recorded in writing in 1826. It is widely used to greet others and initiate conversation[1]. 

Additionally, "Hello" is famously known as the title of popular songs by artists like Adele (released in 2015) and Lionel Richie, both of which have had significant cultural impact[3][4]. 

In computing, "Hello, World!" is a traditional simple program used to introduce beginners to programming languages by displaying the phrase on screen[1]. 

If you meant something else by "hello," please specify!
